First, identify the current debt (short-term liabilities) from the balance sheet:
- Accounts Payable = 545,000.00
- Taxes Payable = 284,755.77

Total current debt = Accounts Payable + Taxes Payable
= 545,000.00 + 284,755.77
= 829,755.77

Next, determine the total cash and cash equivalents available:
- Cash on Hand = 3,730,866.78
- Bank Deposits = 3,938,781.80
- Interest Receivable = 10,811.11
- Accounts Receivable = 1,562,598.26

Total cash and cash equivalents:
= 3,730,866.78 + 3,938,781.80 + 10,811.11 + 1,562,598.26
= 9,243,057.95

Now, calculate the Cash to Current Debt Ratio:
= Cash and Cash Equivalents / Current Debt
= 9,243,057.95 / 829,755.77 â‰ˆ 11.13

Rounded to two decimal places, approximately 11.13.
